main event: A bright object was observed for 1 second at high altitude with tremendous speed, believed to be a meteor.
interesting points: The object was very bright and had tremendous speed at a very high altitude.
The object was believed to be a meteorite.
The sighting was reported through the Electrical Report from the Centennial Ranger Station in the Medicine Bow area.
The report was addressed to the Directorate of Intelligence: U.F.O.B.
sighted object: A bright, fast-moving object at high altitude
location: Centennial Ranger Station, Medicine Bow area
